<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_generating_one_multi_order_per_customer">3.2. Generating one multi-order per customer</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Open a specific customer data record to generate a multi-invoice for this customer.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/order-processing/orders/assets/EN-Orders-Multi-Orders-02.png" alt="EN Orders Multi Orders 02">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 2: generating a multi-order</em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There you will find the function directly in the header of the <strong>Customer data</strong> tab. Click on the <strong>Multi-order</strong> icon to generate a multi-order that includes all of the currently unpaid orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
